The Nigerian Society of Engineers (NSE) has called on the government to carry registered engineers in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) along in the development of the territory, in order to ensure professionalism in the developmental processes. Chairman of the Maitama branch of NSE, Engr. Markus Dye, who made this appeal during a courtesy visit to the President and Chairman in Council, the Nigerian Society of Engineers, Engr. Babagana Mohammed FNSE by the Executive members of NSE Maitama branch, led by the Chairman. Dye said that the purpose of the visit was to formally felicitate with the NSE President on his assumption of office as the 32nd President of NSE, and to pledge their continued support of the Branch for the President’s programmes. According to the NSE Maitama branch chairman, with the assumption of office of the President, he believes that registered engineers will be given their rightful place in the development of the nation and FCT in particular. He further updated the president on the activities of the Branch which involved preparations towards the forthcoming 1st World Engineering Day, scheduled to be celebrated worldwide on March 4, 2020, which includes Engineering career seminars and STEM workshops for students at various secondary school in the FCT. The President of the Nigerian Society of Engineers, Engr. Babagana Mohammed commended the Maitama branch of the society for leading role in sustainable development, especially in upholding the dignity of Engineering profession. Mohammed said his administration has come with a strong purpose to rally all members and give everybody a sense of belonging, thereby making the society one big strong family, united in purpose. He solicited the support of every member of the society in helping achieve that aspiration, as well as promotes sustainable development of Nigeria.